replies.body:
Two different ways I could see Garen changing with regards to an ultimate; 

AoE melee execute; if Darius is a guillotine, then Garen is a propeller - his signature "spin to win" is used for one massive swing that cuts down enemies in an arc for huge damage. The ability no longer deals damage based on missing health, but gains AoE as a result. Would make Garen less frustrating to play against when building defense, and give him some additional team-fight power. 

The commander; The might of Demacia commands his allies forward, giving them a movement-speed boost and armor/resist based on his bonus defenses.  This would give Garen massive team-fight utility, play into his theme as a great general of Demacia. Suddenly his strength wouldn't entirely lie on his ability to kill a single target, but also in how he leads his allies to victory with a group ultimate. A bit of overlap with Sivir here, but given that she's the only champion in the game with a team-steroid, Garen might be good candidate for another.
